remarks: No wind speed recorded at this point.
Pt 1 min 5 BBCU-- I walked towards it after the count to confirm ID and it flew right over! Visual check on distant FISP (133m) confirmed at this time too.

EASO pt 9 min 6 call was strange| short| very widely-spaced version of the 'trill' call-- ~4 notes 1/2 second spaced and fading away. Given in response to SERIOUS mobbing action by songbirds. Mobbing began in min 5| continued aggressively and persistently through end of min 6 and after. Call finally heard ~30 sec into min 6. Approached afterwards| visually confirmed red-morph EASO.
Pt 1 CONI 'V' detection at 29m| bird was perched on a fence post when I arrived and remained silent and motionless through count.
